@regression
Feature: Skills do not force Opus model usage

  Background:
    Given the nmg-sdlc plugin is installed in Claude Code

  Scenario: No skill forces Opus model
    When the SKILL.md frontmatter of all skills is examined
    Then no skill has "model: opus" in its frontmatter

  Scenario: Complex skills inherit session model
    Given the user's Claude Code session is using any model
    When "implementing-specs" or "writing-specs" is invoked
    Then the skill inherits the session model
    And there is no "model" field in the skill's frontmatter

  Scenario: Template-based skills use Sonnet
    Given the skills "migrating-projects", "running-retrospectives", and "setting-up-steering"
    When their SKILL.md frontmatter is examined
    Then each has "model: sonnet"

  Scenario: Slash-command-only skills are not auto-triggerable
    Given the skills "running-sdlc-loop", "installing-openclaw-skill", "generating-openclaw-config", and "running-retrospectives"
    When the plugin is loaded
    Then each has "disable-model-invocation: true" in its frontmatter
    And their descriptions are not included in the available skills list

  Scenario: Auto-triggerable skills remain discoverable
    Given the skills "creating-issues", "implementing-specs", "starting-issues", "verifying-specs", and "writing-specs"
    When the plugin is loaded
    Then each does not have "disable-model-invocation: true"
    And their descriptions appear in the available skills list
